{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17627103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17627103"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:44:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:44:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17103"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17103"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.16,0.04,0.63,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9793"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77499"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9793","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9793"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17103"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63011"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5025"},{"type":"tags","id":"5049"},{"type":"tags","id":"8412"},{"type":"tags","id":"8452"},{"type":"tags","id":"11215"},{"type":"tags","id":"11216"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22971"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23147"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77499","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77499"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EMagnesium sulphate is an important medication used in several acute medical conditions including pre-eclampsia and cardiac arrhythmias.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary mechanism of action of magnesium sulphate as a smooth muscle relaxant?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Blocks sodium channels and reduces intracellular sodium","Activates potassium channels causing hyperpolarisation","Inhibits release of inflammatory mediators","Inhibits calcium channels and reduces intracellular calcium","Enhances gamma-aminobutyric acid receptor function"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary mechanism of action of magnesium sulphate is to \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibit calcium channels and reduce intracellular calcium\u003C/strong\u003E. This leads to smooth muscle relaxation and various therapeutic effects including vasodilation and bronchodilation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect mechanisms can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks sodium channels and reduces intracellular sodium\u003C/strong\u003E: magnesium has minimal effects on sodium channels and this is not a clinically significant mechanism of action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EActivates potassium channels causing hyperpolarisation\u003C/strong\u003E: while magnesium is important for normal potassium channel function, channel activation is not responsible for its therapeutic effects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibiting release of inflammatory mediators\u003C/strong\u003E: any anti-inflammatory effects of magnesium are secondary to its calcium channel blocking properties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnhancing gamma-aminobutyric acid receptor function\u003C/strong\u003E: magnesium does not have significant direct effects on GABA neurotransmission.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBy reducing intracellular calcium, magnesium sulphate decreases smooth muscle contraction, which explains its effectiveness in conditions like pre-eclampsia (reducing vasospasm) and severe asthma (bronchodilation). It also stabilises cardiac cell membranes, making it useful in treating certain arrhythmias.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Magnesium sulfate acts as a calcium channel blocker, reducing intracellular calcium and causing smooth muscle relaxation.","Magnesium sulfate is used clinically for multiple pathologies including treatment of pre-eclampsia, severe asthma, and torsade de pointes."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63011"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17103"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63011","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63011"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T10:12:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-07T10:12:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9793"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77499"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":nu